text: Mari-Liis Lillemäe (born 1 September 2000) is an Estonian footballer who plays as a midfielder for Naiste Meistriliiga club FC Flora and the Estonia women's national team. ==Career== Lillemäe has been capped for the Estonia national team, appearing for the team during the UEFA Women's Euro 2021 qualifying cycle. ==References== ==External links== * * * * Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:People from Viljandi Parish Category:Estonian women's footballers Category:Estonia women's international footballers Category:Women's association football midfielders
